      "message": "currently in every place in code which writes the response status, it must not forget to also save the status for the metric. I find this a bit fragile, it is easy to forget to do it.\n\nI recommend to wrap http.ResponseWrapper, override only WriteStatus and capture there, while not overriding other functions:\n\n  type resWriter struct {\n    http.ResponseWriter\n    status int64\n  }\n\n  func (w *resWriter) WriteStatus(status int) {\n    w.status \u003d status\n    w.ResponseWriter.WriteStatus(status)\n  }\n\n  resW :\u003d \u0026resWriter{Writer: c.Writer}\n  c.Writer \u003d resW\n  defer resW.Close() // writes the metrics\n  \n  ",
